==English==

===Verb===
'''[[set]] [[off]]'''

# {{idiom}} To [[leave]]; to begin a [[journey]] or [[trip]].
#: ''He '''set off''' in search of better opportunities.''
# {{idiom}} To [[begin]]; to [[cause]]; to [[initiate]].
#: ''I had no idea that one simple comment would '''set off''' such a huge argument.''
